e impact of natural forces on premodern society was tremendous, if not catastrophic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aFrühe Neuzeit /Kultur. 4aLändlicher Raum. 4aMittelalter /Literatur. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aEarly Modern Age.  aMedieval Culture.  aMiddle Ages.  aRural Space.1 aApplauso, Nicolino, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBreeze, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrugger, Eveline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChesney Zegura, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClason, Christopher R.1 aClason, Christopher R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClassen, Albrecht, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClassen, Albrecht, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDiRoberto, Kyle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDowling, Abigail P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJasper, Kathryn L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJost, Jean E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Sharon D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoffitt Peacock, Martha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlson, Sherri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPerez, Rosa A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPigg, Daniel F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoss, Lia B., econtributor.4ctb4htt